What is IP address ?

An IP address (Internet Protocol address) is a unique identifier assigned to each device connected to a network that uses the Internet Protocol for communication.

ðŸ”¹ Types of IP Addresses:
IPv4 (e.g., 192.168.1.1)

Most commonly used

32-bit address (about 4.3 billion unique addresses)

IPv6 (e.g., 2001:0db8:85a3:0000:0000:8a2e:0370:7334)

Newer standard

128-bit address (trillions of possible addresses)

Created to deal with the shortage of IPv4 addresses

ðŸ”¹ Two Main Categories:
Private IP Address:

Used inside a local network (home, office)

Not visible to the internet

Example: 192.168.x.x, 10.x.x.x, 172.16.x.x

Public IP Address:

Assigned by your Internet Service Provider (ISP)

Used to identify your device on the internet

Can be static (fixed) or dynamic (changes over time)

ðŸ”¹ What Itâ€™s Used For:
Identifies your device on a network

Enables devices to communicate with each other

Required for accessing the internet or other network services
